# RTL (Right-to-Left) Support Rules

## Overview

This app supports dynamic RTL/LTR switching with language persistence via AsyncStorage.

## Languages

- **English (en)**: LTR (Left-to-Right)
- **Hebrew (he)**: RTL (Right-to-Left)

## Implementation

### Language Persistence

Language preference is saved to AsyncStorage and loaded on app start:

```typescript
// Saved to: @app_language
// Values: 'en' | 'he'

// On app start
await initializeLanguage(); // Loads saved language

// When user changes language
const needsRestart = await changeLanguage('he'); // Saves to AsyncStorage
```

### RTL Direction Control

Using React Native's `I18nManager`:

```typescript
import { I18nManager } from 'react-native';

const isRTL = language === 'he';
I18nManager.forceRTL(isRTL);
```

### Automatic Behavior

When Hebrew is selected:
- ✅ Text direction: RTL
- ✅ Layout direction: RTL
- ✅ Navigation: RTL
- ✅ Flexbox: RTL
- ✅ Margins/Padding: Flipped
- ✅ Preference: Persisted

## App Restart

**IMPORTANT:** RTL changes require app restart to fully apply.

User sees alert: "Please close and reopen the app for the language change to take full effect."

## NativeWind & RTL

NativeWind automatically handles RTL transformations:

```typescript
// LTR (English):
<View className="ml-4">  // margin-left: 16px

// RTL (Hebrew):
<View className="ml-4">  // margin-right: 16px (auto-flipped!)
```

### What Gets Auto-Flipped

✅ **Margins:**
- `ml-*` ↔ `mr-*`
- `mx-*` (stays same)

✅ **Padding:**
- `pl-*` ↔ `pr-*`
- `px-*` (stays same)

✅ **Flexbox:**
- `flex-row` (reverses direction)
- `flex-row-reverse` (reverses direction)

✅ **Text Alignment:**
- `text-left` ↔ `text-right`
- `text-center` (stays same)

✅ **Borders:**
- `border-l-*` ↔ `border-r-*`

### What Does NOT Get Flipped

❌ **Absolute Positioning:**
- `left-*` / `right-*` (use with caution)

❌ **Border Radius:**
- `rounded-tl-*` / `rounded-tr-*` (specific corners)

❌ **Transform:**
- `translate-x-*` (manual handling needed)

## CRITICAL Rules for RTL Support

### ✅ DO: Use NativeWind Classes

```typescript
// ✅ CORRECT - Auto-flips in RTL
<View className="ml-4 pl-2">
<Text className="text-left">Text</Text>
<View className="flex-row">
```

### ❌ DON'T: Use Inline Styles with Directional Properties

```typescript
// ❌ WRONG - Breaks RTL
<View style={{ marginLeft: 16 }}>
<View style={{ paddingRight: 8 }}>
<View style={{ left: 0 }}>
<View style={{ textAlign: 'left' }}>
```

### ✅ DO: Use Theme Colors

```typescript
// ✅ CORRECT
import { colors } from '../../theme';
<ActivityIndicator color={colors.primary} />
```

### ❌ DON'T: Hardcode Colors

```typescript
// ❌ WRONG
<ActivityIndicator color="#3B82F6" />
```

## Testing Checklist

### Manual Testing

Test EVERY screen in both languages:

1. **Switch to Hebrew:**
   - Go to Profile → Tap "עברית"
   - Close and reopen app
   - Verify RTL layout

2. **Verify Each Screen:**
   - [ ] Text flows right-to-left
   - [ ] Navigation mirrors correctly
   - [ ] Buttons align properly
   - [ ] Lists display correctly
   - [ ] Forms work properly
   - [ ] Modals/Alerts display correctly

3. **Switch to English:**
   - Go to Profile → Tap "English"
   - Close and reopen app
   - Verify LTR layout

### Automated Testing

```typescript
// Test language persistence
const savedLang = await getSavedLanguage();
expect(savedLang).toBe('he');

// Test RTL setting
expect(I18nManager.isRTL).toBe(true);
```

## Common RTL Issues & Solutions

### Issue: Layout Breaks in RTL

**Cause:** Using inline styles with left/right properties

**Solution:** Use NativeWind classes
```typescript
// ❌ WRONG
<View style={{ marginLeft: 10 }}>

// ✅ CORRECT
<View className="ml-2.5">
```

### Issue: Icons Don't Flip

**Cause:** Icons that should mirror (arrows, chevrons) don't flip

**Solution:** Use `transform: scaleX(-1)` conditionally
```typescript
import { I18nManager } from 'react-native';

<Icon 
  name="arrow-right" 
  style={{ transform: [{ scaleX: I18nManager.isRTL ? -1 : 1 }] }}
/>
```

### Issue: Text Alignment Wrong

**Cause:** Hardcoded text alignment

**Solution:** Use NativeWind classes
```typescript
// ❌ WRONG
<Text style={{ textAlign: 'left' }}>

// ✅ CORRECT
<Text className="text-left">  // Auto-flips to text-right in RTL
```

## Best Practices

### 1. Always Use NativeWind

```typescript
// ✅ CORRECT
<View className="flex-1 bg-white p-4">
  <Text className="text-lg font-bold mb-2">Title</Text>
</View>
```

### 2. Import Theme Colors

```typescript
// ✅ CORRECT
import { colors } from '../../theme';
<ActivityIndicator color={colors.primary} />
```

### 3. Test in Both Languages

- Develop in English
- Test in Hebrew before committing
- Check all screens, not just the one you changed

### 4. Use Flexbox for Layouts

```typescript
// ✅ CORRECT - Auto-adapts to RTL
<View className="flex-row items-center justify-between">
  <Text>Start</Text>
  <Text>End</Text>
</View>
```

### 5. Avoid Absolute Positioning

```typescript
// ⚠️ USE WITH CAUTION
<View className="absolute left-0">  // Won't flip in RTL

// ✅ BETTER
<View className="absolute" style={{ [I18nManager.isRTL ? 'right' : 'left']: 0 }}>
```

## Language Switching Flow

```
User taps language button
  ↓
changeLanguage('he') called
  ↓
i18next updates text
  ↓
I18nManager.forceRTL(true)
  ↓
AsyncStorage.setItem('@app_language', 'he')
  ↓
Returns: needsRestart = true
  ↓
Alert shown: "Restart Required"
  ↓
User closes app
  ↓
User reopens app
  ↓
initializeLanguage() called
  ↓
AsyncStorage.getItem('@app_language')
  ↓
Returns: 'he'
  ↓
i18next.changeLanguage('he')
  ↓
I18nManager.forceRTL(true)
  ↓
App renders in Hebrew with RTL layout ✅
```

## Debugging RTL Issues

### Check Current RTL State

```typescript
import { I18nManager } from 'react-native';

console.log('Is RTL:', I18nManager.isRTL);
console.log('Current language:', i18n.language);
```

### Check Saved Language

```typescript
import AsyncStorage from '@react-native-async-storage/async-storage';

const saved = await AsyncStorage.getItem('@app_language');
console.log('Saved language:', saved);
```

### Force RTL for Testing

```typescript
// In App.tsx (temporary, for testing)
I18nManager.forceRTL(true);
```

